### FindFirstMatchingPrefix() {#a02aebfa7014b1bf9a52445a58163adb8}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static std::pair&lt; StringRef, StringRef &gt; FindFirstMatchingPrefix (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/filecheckrequest">FileCheckRequest</a> &amp; Req, <a href="/docs/api/structs/prefixmatcher">PrefixMatcher</a> &amp; Matcher, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> &amp; Buffer, unsigned &amp; LineNumber, Check::FileCheckType &amp; CheckTy)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Searches the buffer for the first prefix in the prefix regular expression.

This searches the buffer using the provided regular expression, however it enforces constraints beyond that: 1) The found prefix must not be a suffix of something that looks like a valid prefix. 2) The found prefix must be followed by a valid check type suffix using <code>FindCheckType</code> above.


<SectionUser title="Returns">
a pair of StringRefs into the Buffer, which combines:
<ul>
<li>the first match of the regular expression to satisfy these two is returned, otherwise an empty <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> is returned to indicate failure.</li>
<li>buffer rewound to the location right after parsed suffix, for parsing to continue from</li>
</ul>
</SectionUser>

If this routine returns a valid prefix, it will also shrink <code>Buffer</code> to start at the beginning of the returned prefix, increment <code>LineNumber</code> for each new line consumed from <code>Buffer</code>, and set <code>CheckTy</code> to the type of check found by examining the suffix.

If no valid prefix is found, the state of Buffer, LineNumber, and CheckTy is unspecified.

Definition at line <a href="#l01717">1717</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/filecheck/filecheck-cpp">FileCheck.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

<Link id="l01693" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1693"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Searches the buffer for the first prefix in the prefix regular expression.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01694" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1694"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01695" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1695"><Highlight kind="comment">/// This searches the buffer using the provided regular expression, however it</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01696" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1696"><Highlight kind="comment">/// enforces constraints beyond that:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01697" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1697"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 1) The found prefix must not be a suffix of something that looks like</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01698" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1698"><Highlight kind="comment">///    a valid prefix.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01699" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1699"><Highlight kind="comment">/// 2) The found prefix must be followed by a valid check type suffix using \\c</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01700" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1700"><Highlight kind="comment">///    FindCheckType above.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01701" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1701"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01702" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1702"><Highlight kind="comment">/// \\returns a pair of StringRefs into the Buffer, which combines:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01703" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1703"><Highlight kind="comment">///   - the first match of the regular expression to satisfy these two is</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01704" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1704"><Highlight kind="comment">///   returned,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01705" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1705"><Highlight kind="comment">///     otherwise an empty StringRef is returned to indicate failure.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01706" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1706"><Highlight kind="comment">///   - buffer rewound to the location right after parsed suffix, for parsing</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01707" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1707"><Highlight kind="comment">///     to continue from</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01708" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1708"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01709" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1709"><Highlight kind="comment">/// If this routine returns a valid prefix, it will also shrink \\p Buffer to</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01710" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1710"><Highlight kind="comment">/// start at the beginning of the returned prefix, increment \\p LineNumber for</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01711" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1711"><Highlight kind="comment">/// each new line consumed from \\p Buffer, and set \\p CheckTy to the type of</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01712" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1712"><Highlight kind="comment">/// check found by examining the suffix.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01713" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1713"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01714" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1714"><Highlight kind="comment">/// If no valid prefix is found, the state of Buffer, LineNumber, and CheckTy</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l01715" /><CodeLine lineNumber="1715"><Highlight kind="comment">/// is unspecified.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
